				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Coke ash, also referred to as coal combustion residuals or CCRs, is produced primarily from the burning of coal in coal-fired power plants. It includes a number of by-products produced from burning coal, such as fly ash and bottom ash. Coke ash is conducive to slurrying, as the ash content in coal helps to reduce slurry viscosity and improve stability. By gasification of the coke slurry, many important products, including hydrogen, liquid fuels and chemicals, can be obtained.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">焦炭灰，又称燃煤残渣或 CCR，主要产生于燃煤发电厂的燃煤过程。它包括燃煤产生的一些副产品，如粉煤灰和底灰。焦炭灰有利于浆化，因为煤中的灰分有助于降低浆液粘度并提高稳定性。通过对焦炭浆进行气化，可以获得许多重要产品，包括氢气、液体燃料和化学品。</common:generalComment>
